=TITLE Gnome::Gtk4::R-ShortcutManager
=head1 Description

The L<Gnome::Gtk4::R-ShortcutManager|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/R-ShortcutManager> interface is used to implement
shortcut scopes.

This is important for L<Gnome::Gtk4::Popover|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gnome::Gtk4::R-Native> widgets that have their
own surface, since the event controllers that are used to implement
managed and global scopes are limited to the same native.

Examples for widgets implementing L<Gnome::Gtk4::R-ShortcutManager|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/R-ShortcutManager> are
L<Gnome::Gtk4::Window|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/Window> and L<Gnome::Gtk4::Popover|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/Popover>.

Every widget that implements L<Gnome::Gtk4::R-ShortcutManager|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/R-ShortcutManager> will be used as a
C<GTK_SHORTCUT_SCOPE_MANAGED>.

